<TITLE> Dhaka-Lalmonirhat trains resume after 8 hours </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Lalmonirhat, Dec 25 (bdnews24.com)--Dhaka-Lalmonirhat train service remained snapped for eight hours from 1:30pm on Friday when a train derailed in Lalmonirhat. Rail link between Lalmonirhat and Dhaka, Burhimari, Shantahar and Parbartipur was restored at 9:30pm after the rescue operations started at 5pm, Divisional Railway Traffic (DRT) manager Syed Jahurul Islam said. The crash took place in Mostofi area between Teesta Railway Station and Mohendra Nagar in Lalmonirhat Sadar Upazila as intercity train '750 One Up's engine along with four other carriages derailed earlier. The train was going from Dhaka. After the crash, five men Rafiqul Islam, 55, Abdul Karim, 45, Azizul Islam, 25, Shahana Begum, 40, and Moriam, 10, were admitted to Lalmonirhat Sadar Hospital and others received only primary aid. The train was running faster than the recommended speed, DRT manager Islam said and added the rail line between Teesta and Lalmonirhat was risky. bdn
